== Lunch: Sweet Soy Meatballs & Buttery Rice ==

Wash and dry produce. Thinly slice @Mini Cucumber{1} into rounds. Halve
@Orange{1}; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve
@Red Grapes{2.25%ounce} if desired.

Halve @Fully Cooked Beef Meatballs{8%ounce}. Heat a drizzle of
@Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium
heat. Add meatballs and cook, turning occasionally, until warmed through
and lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Drizzle @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon} over meatballs; stir to coat. Cook
until sauce is warmed through, about ~{30%seconds}. Remove from heat.

While meatballs cook, massage @Microwavable Rice{1} in package to break up
grains; snip to partially open. Microwave for ~{90%seconds}. Add
@Butter{1%tablespoon}. Fluff with a fork until butter melts; season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 6 servings, use 2 tablespoon butter instead of 1.

To serve: Divide rice between plates; top with saucy meatballs and serve
with cucumber rounds, orange slices, and grapes on the side.

> To stash: Let meatballs and rice cool completely. Refrigerate meatballs,
> rice, cucumber rounds, orange slices, and grapes in separate containers and
> pack as desired for lunch!

== Snack: Cinnamon-Sugar Pretzel Bites with Peachy Yogurt Dipper ==

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a large
#microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until butter melts, ~{30-45%seconds}.
Add @Sugar{2%teaspoon} and @Cinnamon{1/2%teaspoon} to same bowl; whisk to
combine.

> For 6 servings, use 4 tablespoon butter, 3 teaspoon sugar, and 3/4 teaspoon
> cinnamon instead.

Add @Pretzel Bites{6%ounce} to bowl with cinnamon-sugar butter; toss to
evenly coat.

Spread out coated pretzel bites in a single layer on a #baking sheet{}
(drizzle any remaining cinnamon-sugar butter over top). Bake on middle
rack until lightly glazed and warmed through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Yogurt{6%tablespoon} and
@Peach Jam{1} until combined.

Serve cinnamon-sugar pretzel bites with peachy yogurt dipper.

> To store: Keep pretzel bites in an airtight container at room temperature.
> Refrigerate peachy yogurt dipper in a separate airtight container.